The paper deals with distributed signal recovery in sensor networks, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and networking (cs.NI) aspects. The algorithm proposed is based on Iterative Hard Thresholding (IHT), which is a popular method in the field of compressed sensing (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the use of solutions to the distributed top-K problem in the database literature, which falls under the category of distributed systems (cs.SY) and databases (cs.DB).
